After all these years of CrossFit (8 to be exact), I must have done thousands of burpees. But I just started experiencing knee pain while doing them. And while recording them in a workout the other day, I was shocked to find what my movement mechanics actually looked like. You‚Äôll see in the video on the left.
-
‚ñ™Ô∏èI have a really wide jumping and landing base because it‚Äôs faster for competition.
-
‚ñ™Ô∏èWhich causes knee valgus (knees caving in) when I jump.
-
‚ñ™Ô∏èWhen landing from my jump I have an even wider base with my hips and feet externally rotated (pointed outwards).
-
‚ñ™Ô∏èTo reset my body position before the next rep I internally rotate my hips, knees, and feet (causing pain in my knees).
-

Since burpees are such a simple exercise I never realized the importance of proper movement mechanics while doing them. But now I‚Äôm hoping to make these adjustments (on the right) to keep me healthy and injury free. Just thought it was kind of interested, so the next time you do them, take a closer look at yourself and your athletes üëåüèΩ #burpees #crossfit #health #fitness #movementmechanics
